data.description: The allure of another era is seamlessly integrated with modern convenience in this delightful Folk Victorian home. Graced with three elegantly covered porches from which to watch the comings and goings around uptown Jackson and the nearby city park, all within a leisurely stroll. The home captures the essence of bygone days with its classic architectural details (e.g., stained glass, refinished hardwoods, original millwork), yet provides peace of mind through recent updates/upgrades including, but not limited to, the following: electrical service, windows, roof, gutter guards, siding & basement pavers, vinyl side porch, furnace, Carolina carport, water heater, water softener & plumbing, paint throughout storage shed, and tree/stump removal. Below, a full utility basement offers abundant storage possibilities while, above, the expansive corner lot affords sweeping views of the suburban landscape. Seize a rare opportunity to own a piece of Jackson history.
